metadata.name: The Music Man
metadata.description:
In downtown Minneapolis there used to be an older gentlemen that would play saxophone on Nicollet Avenue. He is blind and just loved to play and listen to the sounds of the saxophone bounce off the walls of the city skyscrapers. I caught him playing one night while photographing downtown and couldn't miss the opportunity to memorialize him forever.

Edition: 1 of 1

Artist: Tyler James
